article.headline: Idaho State 89, South Dakota St 72
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Junior center Kasey Winters scored a career-high 27 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and senior guard David Schroeder added a season-high 22 points as Idaho State defeated South Dakota State 89-72 Wednesday night. Schroeder was 6-of-10 from 3-point range. Idaho State (9-9) went inside to Winters early and he responded by scoring eight of his team's first 11 points. He finished the first half with 18. South Dakota State (5-13) kept the game close in the opening stages, however, and led by as many as four points on two occasions. Idaho State grabbed control midway through the first half, going on a 16-4 run during one seven-minute stretch and opening a 35-27 lead. South Dakota State kept pace the rest of the half, and Idaho State held a 43-36 lead at halftime. In the second half, the Bengals slowly extended their lead, and it reached 18 points on a free throw by Winters with just under 10 minutes to play. The Jackrabbits answered with an eight-point run to cut the lead to 81-71 with 7:20 left in the game, but that was as close as South Dakota State would get. The Bengals were up by 20 in the final minute. A late 3-pointer from South Dakota State's Eric Heien closed the final margin to 89-72. Tim Henry chipped in 15 points for Idaho State and Slim Millien blocked six shots. South Dakota State had three players in double figures, including a season-high 15 points from Michael Loney, 13 points from Matt Cadwell and 12 points from Mohamed Berte.
